 Comedian Dave Chappelle Hollywood comedian and actor Dave Chappelle has reportedly tested positive for coronavirus which has forced the comedian to cancel his remaining shows in Texas. Reports from the camp of the comedian indicates he is in isolation and has not yet experienced any symptoms for the time been. Dave performed his first of the five scheduled shows in Texas on Wednesday and was billed to perform on Thursday, Friday, Saturday and on Sunday. Organizers of the show are in the process of refunding tickets sales back to the audience.